\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0 At the time of writing, the recommended method for audio playback of Calliope documents is by means of MIDI.  The playback facilities of Calliope are intended primarily for `proof listening', and are not intended to replace sequencers or performance.   Calliope observes the following musical annotations during playback:\par
\pard\tx360\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi-230\sb80\sa0\li360\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0 ·	the modern rules for accidentals (including editorial accidentals). The modern rule is that accidentals remain in effect until cancelled by a barline or superceded by an accidental at the same pitch\up6\fs20 \up0 .\par
\pard\tx360\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi-230\sb80\sa0\li360\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0 ·	grace notes;\par
\pard\tx360\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi-230\sb80\sa0\li360\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0 ·	tied pairs of notes;\par
\pard\tx360\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi-230\sb80\sa0\li360\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0 ·	metronome marks;\par
\pard\tx360\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi-230\sb80\sa0\li360\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0 ·	proportionality constants where these are defined by time signatures.\par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0 In addition, tablature and neumes are played back.  However, Calliope does not observe expression or articulation marks (such as \i\b cres\i0\b0 ., staccato, etc.), or repeat signs.\par
\pard\tx1440\tx2880\tx4320\tx5760\qj\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0 For best results, it is important to bear in mind how the score is going to be performed.  The idea is that each \i note\i0  is associated with a \i part\i0 , which in turn is performed by an \i instrument\i0 , which in turn causes MIDI messages to be sent over one of 16 \i channels\i0  to the MIDI device. You may set the audio parameters of each channel independently before the performance. Although this way of doing things may be overridden (for example, so that notes may individually send control change messages directly to channel 1), writing your music document according to parts and instruments is the recommended way.  Refer to the documentation sections on Parts and Instruments if you are not familiar with them.  Ensure that you have defined the required parts, instruments and channels, and have assigned parts to staves or notes, using the Part Inspector, Instrumentation Inspector and System Inspector.\par
\pard\tx520\tx1060\tx1600\tx2120\tx2660\tx3200\tx3720\tx4260\tx4800\tx5320\qj\fi0\sb80\sa0\li0\ri0\f0\fs24\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\scaps0\cf0 Another consideration is the connection of the computer to a MIDI device.  One such possible configuration is illustrated as follows:\par
